  {
    "p": "/message/content/parts/0",
    "o": "append",
    "v": " introduced, choose high-quality programming and use it together with an adult.\n- **2–5 years:**"
  },
  {
    "v": " Prioritize educational content and maintain reasonable limits.\n- **School-age children and teens"
  },
  {
    "v": ":** Focus on healthy routines rather than strict hourly caps, ensuring screens do not interfere with sleep, exercise,"
  },
  {
    "v": " learning, and social relationships.\n\n## Current scientific consensus\nThe peer-reviewed literature increasingly supports a nuanced"
  },
  {
    "v": " view:\n\n> Screens are tools, not inherently harmful or beneficial.\n\nThe strongest evidence of"
